{
  "stem": "1799.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 76.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] Later on, in the last camp in and around Dachau is when my function, just before we were liberated, when I was the leader of what was called a Totenkommando.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Totenkommando was a contingent of six or eight people that buried corpses daily.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "By this time, conditions were so bad and so awful everywhere, and people were dying not because they were gassed or that they were beaten, but because they were sick, and because no one took care of them.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They just-- they just died because there was no medical attention.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Either they were sick from dysentery, dysentery, or they were sick for other reasons.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's hard to say.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I can't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 58,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "God must have been watching over me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I felt-- I had a strong faith.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I felt, as I mentioned before, that this inhumane-- to put it mildly-- set of conditions could not last.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was doomed to end.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was only praying that I could outlast that period until the ending took place, which fortunately I did.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I was never really beaten.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was once caught having stolen some apples along with two or three other inmates, which I did.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 61,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think I was beaten, but it wasn't-- it wasn't life-threatening.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 62,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, I was always able to get extra food.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, for instance, the apples I mentioned, and I was able to sometimes get potatoes that were kept in a certain place.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I would get-- they were raw potatoes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 63,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Especially in this last camp that I was in after Kaufering, we would take potatoes and roast them, and supplement our food-- roast them in little heaps of fire that we made.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 64,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, this-- I must say that this happened after the Germans had left.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
